# W46 eval API keys — COPY THIS FILE to `eval/.env.eval` and fill in real keys.
# `eval/.env.eval` is gitignored (never committed); this `.example` is the template.
#
# Use THROWAWAY/TEST keys with a low spend cap, not production keys
# (account-risk isolation — see roadmap Decision 13). The whole cost pilot
# spends <$1, so even a $5 provider-side cap is ample headroom.
#
# One key per provider covers all four pilot models:
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY → claude-haiku-4-5 + claude-sonnet-4-6
#   OPENAI_API_KEY    → gpt-5.4 + gpt-5.4-mini
#
# Then run:  npm run eval        (loads this file via tsx --env-file)
# Dry-run (no keys needed):  npm run eval:dry

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=   # not used in the cost pilot; future full-matrix only
